                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, June 2: Sebi has cleared the Rs 1,154-crore open offer for purchase of a 20 per cent stake in Satyam Computer. Tech Mahindra had announced an open offer through Venturbay Consultants, its acquisition vehicle for Satyam Computer purchase, on April 22 for buying an additional 20 per cent from the shareholders of the IT firm.                            
	 New Delhi, June 2: Global rating agency Fitch has downgraded the credit rating of Unitech Ltd and placed it in the default category. Noting that financial restructuring was essential for Unitech to avoid a default in repayment of debts, the agency said, Fitch has, therefore, treated the restructuring as an effective default.                             
	 New Delhi, June 2: The steel ministry is considering restructuring four of its PSU units  Ferro Scrap Nigam Ltd, Kudremukh Iron Ore Company, MSTC and Hindustan Steel Constructions Ltd  to optimise their functioning and has appointed a committee to suggest ways for it.                             
	 New Delhi, June 2: The State Bank of India today said it could raise Rs 28,000 crore from bonds to meet regulatory capital requirement and to fund business growth during the current fiscal.                                                                                                                           
